 it burn the eyes out of your skull to actually read a thing before commenting on it?</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div><ol class="children"><li class="comment byuser odd alt depth-3 parent " id="comment-7721716" data-sort-time="1553043737"><div id="div-comment-7721716" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>Last of the Shitlords</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/03/19/supreme-court-gives-feds-a-long-leash-to/#comment-7721716">March.19.2019 at 9:02 pm </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Ooh, somebody is a little sensitive today.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div><ol class="children"><li class="comment byuser even depth-4" id="comment-7721718" data-sort-time="1553044076"><div id="div-comment-7721718" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>Last of the Shitlords</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/03/19/supreme-court-gives-feds-a-long-leash-to/#comment-7721718">March.19.2019 at 9:07 pm </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Also, many of us come here for the comments. Not the articles. Although I read this one. And by read, I mean skimmed. And by skimmed, I mean glanced at. And by glanced at, I mean imagined what might be in the article.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser odd alt depth-4" id="comment-7721848" data-sort-time="1553058842"><div id="div-comment-7721848" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>Kazinski</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/03/19/supreme-court-gives-feds-a-long-leash-to/#comment-7721848">March.20.2019 at 1:14 am </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Well the case clearly applies to legal immigrants, you could have at least read that part.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div><